SCALING AGILE — SAFe AND IBM APPROACHES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

SAFe (Scaled Agile Framework):
- Designed for organizations implementing Agile at enterprise scale
- Multiple agile teams form an Agile Release Train (ART)
- ART collaborates cross-functionally to deliver incremental solutions regularly
- Every two weeks, ART meets for a demo with feedback for the next sprint
- IBM uses SAFe on large multi-squad programs

IBM SCALING FACTORS (from IBM's Agile Scaling Model):
IBM recognizes that team size is only one of several scaling challenges:
1. Team size (more than 9 people)
2. Physical distribution (geographically dispersed teams)
3. Organizational distribution (multiple IBM and client orgs)
4. Regulatory compliance requirements
5. Cultural or organizational complexity
6. Technical complexity
7. Enterprise disciplines (architecture, strategic reuse, portfolio management)

Each scaling factor requires tailoring the Agile approach. IBM consultants
assess which factors apply and adjust the methodology accordingly.

