AGILE METRICS IBM USES TO TRACK DELIVERY HEALTH
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

VELOCITY: Story points completed per sprint. Used for forecasting, not
measuring team performance. A team's velocity is internal — never compare
velocity between teams.

SPRINT BURNDOWN: Tracks remaining work in a sprint day by day.
Healthy burndown: gradual, steady decrease.
Red flags: flat burndown (team stuck), sudden drop (scope reduced), spike up
(scope added mid-sprint).

RELEASE BURNUP: Tracks total work completed over time against total scope.
Used for release forecasting and stakeholder communication.

CYCLE TIME: Time from when work starts to when it is done.
Used to identify bottlenecks in the delivery pipeline.

LEAD TIME: Time from when work is requested to when it is delivered.
Includes waiting time in the backlog.

DEFECT ESCAPE RATE: Percentage of defects that reach production vs. caught
in testing. A rising escape rate signals quality process issues.

