COLOCATION AND REMOTE AGILE — IBM GUIDANCE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Colocation enhances team dynamics but is not a requirement. IBM squads may be
fully remote, hybrid, or colocated. Some teams colocate for a week and work
remotely for a week. Others only gather for key Agile ceremonies.

What matters: the squad works out a time and cadence that builds and reinforces
team chemistry. Regular meetups (even virtual) streamline communication and
fuel squad success.

IBM virtual practices: always-on web cameras, virtual retrospective boards
(MURAL, Miro), digital standup tools, and virtual happy hours.

Sourcing talent from different locations reduces costs — some squad members
may reside across dispersed geographic locations. IBM has designed its practices
to work well in this model.

